steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"3dq19","text":"Add   of monopotassium phosphate1 (KH2PO4) to a clean 0.5L bottle.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":32,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":37,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":40,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":4,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"39h73","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d8gmb","text":"1Also referred to as potassium phosphate monobasic","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":0,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"54.2","error":false,"guid":"74EB3470381A11EDB4B56572EAFD10D1","id":0,"label":"±0.5","scientificNotation":false,"unit":6}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5igrv","text":"Add   of dipotassium phosphate2 (K2HPO4) to the bottle.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":30,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":34,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":38,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":4,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"3gank","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3avc3","text":"2Also referred to as potassium phosphate dibasic","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":0,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"17.8","error":false,"guid":"56095B4D381E11ED9A700A58A9FEAC02","id":0,"label":"±0.2","scientificNotation":false,"unit":6}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2beln","text":"Measure   of milliQ water in a measuring cylinder, and add it to the bottle.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":8,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"8t38n","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"500","error":false,"guid":"73A83050381E11EDB4B56572EAFD10D1","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":2}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4tmu3","text":"Shake the bottle vigorously until all crystals are dissolved. This can take a few minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9bit7","text":"If this is the first time you prepare this solution, you can ensure that the pH is around 6 using pH paper or a pH-meter. We usually have a pH between 5.8 and 6. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
